sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119346
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: eCDM8 expression + Theophylline riboswitch tetracycline resistance protein + RFP expression
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: High strength promoter (J119031) and a high strength C dog RBS (J119028) controlling expression of the eCDM8 gene (J100100). The clone also contains theophylline riboswitch D (Part J100065) and tetracycline resistance protein (Part J119140) and RFP expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brandon Grieshaber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J04450
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Contains an IPTG inducible promoter an RBS, RFP, and terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tamar Odle

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119303
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: eCDM8 expression with high promoter and high C dog RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A low promoter, J119030 with a low c.dog J119025, this combination is known as S05011. The eCDM8 gene (J100100) was then inserted into the S05011 vector creating a pSB1A8 plasmid with a low promoter, low c.dog, and the eCDM8 gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Todd Eckdahl, Claire Shinneman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Ribo-TetA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This device contains a synthetic riboswitch that can be used in E. coli. In the presence of theophylline, the transcription of the TetA gene occurs, but in the absence of theophylline, very little transcription takes place. This device contains a modified T5 promoter, which, in the absence of cymR, acts as a strong constitutive promoter. The ribosomal binding site is contained in the riboswitch.
This riboswitch is modified from riboswitch D as described in the paper by Topp et al.
References: Shana Topp, Colleen M. K. Reynoso, Jessica C. Seeliger, Ian S. Goldlust, Shawn K. Desai, Doroth??e Murat, Aimee Shen, Aaron W. Puri, Arash Komeili, Carolyn R. Bertozzi, June R. Scott, and Justin P. Gallivan. Synthetic Riboswitches That Induce Gene Expression in Diverse Bacterial Species. Applied and Environmental Microbiology, 76:23, 7881-7884. December 2010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sachith Dharmasena and Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Constructed using BsaI GGA of PCR products from J100065 and J31007.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BsaI sites were introduced into PCR products, but are not present in the final construct.
